# Append-only JSONL feeds: parallel sessions both append at EOF, which a
# line-based merge always reports as a conflict even though both rows belong.
# `merge=union` keeps both sides' lines — safe ONLY because these files are
# append-only by contract (telemetry/README.md; founding plan §5.2) and each
# row is one self-contained JSON line. Do NOT apply union to files where
# ordering or exclusivity matters.
telemetry/*.jsonl merge=union
